Scalpers caught in the crush
2011-01-21 01:02:39 GMT
BEIJING - Chinese railway police detained 330 people for scalping train tickets on Wednesday, the first day of China's 40-day Spring Festival travel rush, the Ministry of Railways said on Thursday.The 330 detained were involved in 288 cases of ticket scalping, the ministry said without detailing how many tickets were confiscated.Railway police also detected more than 15,000 cases of people trying to take dangerous goods on trains. They also confiscated 1,101 knives.The ministry said it has deployed 70,000 railway police officers along China's 91,000 kilometers of railway lines to ensure smooth and safe journeys.Special staff members are communicating with meteorological authorities and emergency plans will be activated if bad weather is expected.Some 700 million people, or nearly half the nation's population, are expected to travel within the country during the 40-day-long travel period.
